alert.note: Alert for Snohomish (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued December 06 at 4:16AM PST until December 06 at 3:28PM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Washington... Snoqualmie River Near Carnation affecting King County. Snoqualmie River Near Snoqualmie Falls affecting King County. Skykomish River Near Gold Bar affecting Snohomish County. .The upper reaches of the Snoqualmie have already crested this morning. The flood crest will arrive at Carnation this morning. The Skykomish near Goldbar is receding and will continue to recede this morning. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL LATE THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...No flooding is currently forecast. * WHERE...Skykomish River near Gold Bar. * WHEN...Until late this afternoon. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 3:30 AM PST Wednesday the stage was 15.0 feet. - Flood stage is 15.0 feet. - The river crested near 18.0 feet around noon Tuesday. - Forecast...The river will continue receding today. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Be especially cautious at night when it is harder to recognize the dangers of flooding. Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Caution is urged when walking near riverbanks. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued by this afternoon at 1230 PM PST.
